---
import ServicePage from '../layouts/ServicePage.astro';
import ContactForm from '../components/ContactForm.astro';
---

<ServicePage
  title="Local SEO Manchester & Stockport | MM SEO"
  description="Local SEO specialist in Stockport. GBP optimisation, local citations, geo-targeted content for Manchester and the UK."
  canonical="https://www.mmseo.co.uk/local-seo/"
  breadcrumb="Local SEO"
>

  <!-- ── 1. Hero band (dark) ─────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-hero section-dark">
    <div class="container sp-hero-inner reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Local SEO | Manchester, Stockport &amp; UK</p>
      <h1 class="sp-h1">Local SEO: Be Found When It Matters Most</h1>
      <p class="sp-intro">
        When your customers search for businesses like yours in your area, you need to
        appear in the map pack, in organic results, and on the right terms. Local SEO
        is the set of strategies that makes that happen, and it's where I've helped
        businesses in Manchester, Stockport, and across the UK consistently win
        against larger, better-funded competitors.
      </p>
      <a href="/#contact" class="btn-primary">Book a Free Consultation</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 2. Main content (light) ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-content section-light">
    <div class="container sp-content-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2">What Local SEO Involves</h2>

      <p>
        Local SEO is distinct from general organic SEO in that it focuses on ranking
        in geographic searches like "SEO consultant Manchester", "solicitor Stockport",
        "hair salon near me". These searches have extremely high commercial intent,
        which makes local visibility directly tied to enquiries and footfall.
      </p>
      <p>
        The local search ecosystem has three main components: your Google Business
        Profile, your on-site geo-targeted content, and your local citations and
        links. All three need to be strong and consistent for you to compete
        effectively in the map pack and local organic results.
      </p>

      <h3 class="sp-h3">What I do</h3>
      <ul class="sp-list">
        <li><strong>Google Business Profile optimisation</strong>: complete profile setup, category selection, service areas, Q&amp;A, photo strategy, and ongoing management</li>
        <li><strong>NAP consistency audit</strong>: ensuring your Name, Address, and Phone number are consistent across every directory, citation, and listing online</li>
        <li><strong>Local citation building</strong>: strategic submissions to relevant UK business directories and industry-specific platforms</li>
        <li><strong>Geo-targeted on-site content</strong>: location pages and service-area content written for both rankings and conversion</li>
        <li><strong>Local keyword strategy</strong>: mapping geo-specific search terms (near me, city+service) to pages on your site</li>
        <li><strong>Local link acquisition</strong>: building links from local newspapers, business associations, chambers of commerce, and community sites</li>
        <li><strong>Review generation strategy</strong>: a practical approach to ethically generating more Google reviews, which directly influence local pack rankings</li>
        <li><strong>Competitor benchmarking</strong>: understanding exactly what the businesses above you are doing and identifying the gaps we can close</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 3. Why it matters (dark) ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-why section-dark">
    <div class="container sp-why-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2 chalk">Why Local SEO Is a Different Game</h2>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        Local search results are heavily weighted towards proximity, prominence, and
        relevance. A business that has optimised its Google Business Profile and
        built consistent local citations will routinely outrank a larger competitor
        with a stronger national presence, because Google's algorithm for local
        results prioritises trust signals that are specific to the local context.
      </p>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        The map pack (the three Google Business listings that appear before organic
        results) captures a significant share of clicks for local searches. For many
        businesses, appearing in the map pack is more valuable than ranking number
        one organically. I optimise for both, but the map pack is often where the
        fastest wins are found.
      </p>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        I'm based in Marple, Stockport and work extensively with businesses in
        Manchester, Stockport, and the wider Greater Manchester area, though my
        local SEO work extends across the UK. My own local SEO experience means I
        practise exactly what I preach.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 4. What is Local SEO (light) ──────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-content section-light">
    <div class="container sp-content-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2">What is Local SEO and Why Does It Matter?</h2>
      <p>
        Local SEO is the process of optimising your online presence so your business appears
        when people nearby search for your products or services. Unlike national SEO, local SEO
        focuses on geo-specific searches — "SEO consultant near me", "hair salon Manchester",
        "solicitor Stockport" — the kind of searches where proximity and relevance combine to
        determine who wins the customer.
      </p>
      <p>
        For service businesses, tradespeople, professional services firms, and local retailers,
        local SEO is typically the highest-ROI marketing activity available. The searchers are
        already in buying mode. They know what they want. Your job — and mine — is to make sure
        your business appears when they look. A solid local SEO strategy works alongside
        <a href="/seo-strategy/" class="sp-inline-link">SEO strategy</a> and
        <a href="/technical-seo/" class="sp-inline-link">technical SEO</a>
        to build a complete, durable search presence.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 5. Local SEO Services I Provide (dark) ─────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-why section-dark">
    <div class="container sp-why-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2 chalk">Local SEO Services I Provide</h2>

      <h3 class="sp-h3 chalk">Google Business Profile Optimisation</h3>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        Your Google Business Profile (formerly Google My Business) is the single most important
        local SEO asset you have. It determines whether you appear in the Map Pack — the three
        business listings shown above organic results for local searches. I audit and optimise
        every element of your profile: business category, service areas, opening hours, photo
        quality, Q&amp;A, review responses, and posting frequency. A well-optimised GBP can
        move you from invisible to the top three results for searches in your area.
      </p>

      <h3 class="sp-h3 chalk">Local Citation Building</h3>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        Citations are mentions of your business name, address, and phone number (NAP) across
        directories, data aggregators, and local websites. Consistency matters — a single
        discrepancy between "St" and "Street" across 50 directory listings can suppress your
        local rankings. I audit your existing citation profile, correct inconsistencies, and
        build new citations on the directories that carry the most weight in your sector and
        location.
      </p>

      <h3 class="sp-h3 chalk">Location-Specific Content</h3>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        Generic content does not rank for local searches. I create and optimise pages and
        content that signal relevance to your specific geographic area — Manchester, Stockport,
        Cheshire, or wherever your customers are. This includes town and borough-level landing
        pages where appropriate, local schema markup, and content that references the
        communities and areas you serve.
      </p>

      <h3 class="sp-h3 chalk">Local Link Building</h3>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        Links from locally relevant websites — local news outlets, business directories, chamber
        of commerce sites, local blogs — carry significant weight for local rankings. I identify
        and pursue local link opportunities that build your authority within your geographic
        target area.
      </p>

      <h3 class="sp-h3 chalk">Review Strategy</h3>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        Volume and recency of Google reviews directly influence your Map Pack position. I develop
        a review generation strategy that makes it easy for satisfied customers to leave reviews
        — without violating Google's guidelines. More reviews, better ratings, and thoughtful
        responses all contribute to stronger local rankings.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 6. Manchester and Stockport (light) ─────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-content section-light">
    <div class="container sp-content-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2">Local SEO for Manchester and Stockport Businesses</h2>
      <p>
        I'm based in Marple, Stockport — which means I have genuine local knowledge of the
        Greater Manchester market. I understand the competitive landscape for businesses in
        Stockport, Manchester city centre, Salford, Trafford, Cheshire, and the surrounding
        areas.
      </p>
      <p>
        Whether you're a solicitor in Manchester city centre competing for "family solicitor
        Manchester" searches, a hair salon in Stockport targeting "hair salon Stockport", or a
        tradesperson across Greater Manchester trying to dominate near-me searches — I build
        local SEO strategies around your specific location, your specific competitors, and your
        specific customers.
      </p>
      <p>
        As a <strong>local SEO consultant in Stockport</strong> with deep knowledge of the
        Manchester market, I provide <strong>local SEO services in Manchester</strong> and
        across the wider region. Whether you need <strong>local SEO in Stockport</strong> or
        <strong>local SEO consulting in Manchester</strong>, my approach is always grounded in
        the specifics of your geography — not generic templates applied to every client.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 7. Who Benefits Most (dark) ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-why section-dark">
    <div class="container sp-why-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2 chalk">Who Benefits Most from Local SEO?</h2>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        Local SEO delivers the strongest results for businesses where location is a primary
        factor in the customer's decision. This includes:
      </p>
      <ul class="sp-list chalk-list">
        <li>Professional services: solicitors, accountants, financial advisers, surveyors</li>
        <li>Tradespeople: builders, electricians, plumbers, decorators</li>
        <li>Health and beauty: salons, clinics, dentists, physios</li>
        <li>Hospitality: restaurants, cafes, bars, venues</li>
        <li>Retail: local shops, showrooms, outlets</li>
        <li>Estate agents and letting agents</li>
        <li>Any service business where customers search "near me" or include a location in their query</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        If your customers are within a driveable distance and they use Google to find businesses
        like yours, local SEO is the most direct path to more enquiries.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 8. Page FAQ (light) ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-content section-light">
    <div class="container sp-content-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <dl class="page-faq-list">

        <div class="page-faq-item">
          <dt>
            <button class="page-faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="pfaq-0" id="pfaq-btn-0">
              <span class="page-faq-question">How long does local SEO take to show results?</span>
              <span class="page-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round">
                  <line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19" class="pfaq-icon-v"/>
                  <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </button>
          </dt>
          <dd id="pfaq-0" class="page-faq-answer" role="region" aria-labelledby="pfaq-btn-0" hidden>
            <div class="page-faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Google Business Profile improvements can show results within 4–8 weeks. Organic local rankings typically improve meaningfully within 3–6 months of consistent work. The Map Pack is often faster to influence than organic positions.</p>
            </div>
          </dd>
        </div>

        <div class="page-faq-item">
          <dt>
            <button class="page-faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="pfaq-1" id="pfaq-btn-1">
              <span class="page-faq-question">Do I need a physical address to rank locally?</span>
              <span class="page-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round">
                  <line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19" class="pfaq-icon-v"/>
                  <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </button>
          </dt>
          <dd id="pfaq-1" class="page-faq-answer" role="region" aria-labelledby="pfaq-btn-1" hidden>
            <div class="page-faq-answer-inner">
              <p>For Google Business Profile, yes — you need a verifiable business address. For organic local SEO, a service area business without a public-facing premises can still rank for local searches through content and citation strategies.</p>
            </div>
          </dd>
        </div>

        <div class="page-faq-item">
          <dt>
            <button class="page-faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="pfaq-2" id="pfaq-btn-2">
              <span class="page-faq-question">How important are Google reviews for local SEO?</span>
              <span class="page-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round">
                  <line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19" class="pfaq-icon-v"/>
                  <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </button>
          </dt>
          <dd id="pfaq-2" class="page-faq-answer" role="region" aria-labelledby="pfaq-btn-2" hidden>
            <div class="page-faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Very. Review volume, recency, and rating are confirmed ranking factors for the Map Pack. A business with 50 recent reviews will almost always outrank an equivalent business with 5 old reviews, all else being equal.</p>
            </div>
          </dd>
        </div>

        <div class="page-faq-item">
          <dt>
            <button class="page-faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="pfaq-3" id="pfaq-btn-3">
              <span class="page-faq-question">Can you help businesses outside Manchester and Stockport?</span>
              <span class="page-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round">
                  <line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19" class="pfaq-icon-v"/>
                  <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </button>
          </dt>
          <dd id="pfaq-3" class="page-faq-answer" role="region" aria-labelledby="pfaq-btn-3" hidden>
            <div class="page-faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Yes — I work with local businesses across the UK. While I'm based in Stockport, local SEO is a remote-friendly service. I've helped businesses in London, Birmingham, Edinburgh, and across the UK improve their local search presence.</p>
            </div>
          </dd>
        </div>

      </dl>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 9. Contact CTA ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <ContactForm />

</ServicePage>

<style>
  .section-dark  { background-color: var(--ink);  color: var(--chalk); }
  .section-light { background-color: var(--chalk); color: var(--ink); }

  .container {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: clamp(1.25rem, 5vw, 2rem);
  }

  .sp-hero { padding: 5rem 0 4rem; }
  .sp-hero-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .eyebrow {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .sp-h1 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--chalk);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .sp-intro {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(248, 247, 242, 0.75);
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    background-color: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 0.8rem 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease;
    align-self: flex-start;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover { background-color: var(--accent-dk); }

  .sp-content { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .sp-content-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .sp-h2 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .sp-h2.chalk { color: var(--chalk); }

  .sp-h3 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .sp-content p, .sp-content-inner p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.8);
  }

  .sp-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .sp-list li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.8);
  }
  .sp-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .sp-why { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .sp-why-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }
  .chalk { color: var(--chalk); }
  .chalk-muted {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(248, 247, 242, 0.75);
  }

  .sp-h3.chalk { color: var(--chalk); }

  .chalk-list li { color: rgba(248, 247, 242, 0.75); }

  .sp-inline-link {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(255, 104, 38, 0.45);
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .sp-inline-link:hover { color: var(--accent-dk); }

  /* ── Page FAQ ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .page-faq-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .page-faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .page-faq-item:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .page-faq-trigger {
    width: 100%;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    padding: 1.375rem 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .page-faq-question {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: clamp(0.9375rem, 1.2vw, 1.0625rem);
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.4;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .page-faq-icon {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: var(--accent-dk);
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .page-faq-trigger:hover .page-faq-icon {
    background-color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.04);
    border-color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.2);
  }

  .pfaq-icon-v {
    transition: transform 0.25s ease, opacity 0.25s ease;
    transform-origin: center;
  }

  .page-faq-trigger[aria-expanded="true"] .pfaq-icon-v {
    transform: rotate(90deg);
    opacity: 0;
  }

  .page-faq-answer-inner {
    padding-bottom: 1.375rem;
  }

  .page-faq-answer-inner p {
    font-size: clamp(0.9375rem, 1.2vw, 1.0625rem);
    color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.7);
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 65ch;
  }

  .reveal {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(24px);
    transition: opacity 0.55s ease, transform 0.55s ease;
  }
  .reveal.visible {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: none;
  }
</style>

<script>
  const revealEls = document.querySelectorAll('.reveal');
  const io = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => entries.forEach(e => { if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('visible'); io.unobserve(e.target); } }),
    { threshold: 0.12 }
  );
  revealEls.forEach(el => io.observe(el));

  // Page FAQ accordion
  const pageFaqTriggers = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('.page-faq-trigger');
  pageFaqTriggers.forEach((trigger) => {
    trigger.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const expanded = trigger.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
      const answerId = trigger.getAttribute('aria-controls')!;
      const answer = document.getElementById(answerId)!;
      pageFaqTriggers.forEach((t) => {
        if (t !== trigger) {
          t.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
          document.getElementById(t.getAttribute('aria-controls')!)!.hidden = true;
        }
      });
      trigger.setAttribute('aria-expanded', expanded ? 'false' : 'true');
      answer.hidden = expanded;
    });
  });
</script>
